body:
After a lot of debugging I've got some more info:

Essentially the contract:
```
pragma solidity ^0.6.4;
pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;

contract PD {

  struct ReceivedPalletData {
    string did;
    string receivedPalletSsccCode;
    string receivedPalletSsccStatusCode;
    string receivedPalletBarcode;
    string receivedPalletQuantitySu;
    string receivedPalletBestBeforDate;
    string goodsReceiptMessage;
  }

  ReceivedPalletData[] internal _receivedPalletDataRegistry;

  function getContents() public view override returns (ReceivedPalletData[] memory) {
    return _receivedPalletDataRegistry;
  }

}
```

The problem is I cannot tell you how much is in the array since it is hard to get out. But I cannot find any information on there being limits to get data out. Even my logger truncates ;) https://gist.github.com/roderik/c99f345624f95a37c6c386a9c4d9c6f8

Some random things:
- My nodes return data, albeit slowly, with -Xms4g -Xmx4g, but they get killed by hitting the 5gb Kubernetes limit I've set. But Xmx is max VM size, so I thought it would stay at max 4
- I had to increase the Ethers timeout (2min) to a lot higher to get it to wait long enough for the response. 

Some things I've been thinking about:

- the db is stored on a regular persistent disk in google cloud, you can also create ssd persistent disks, that might speed up rocksdb queries?
